        <content type="html"><![CDATA[<p>I keep forgetting how to write MDX blog posts, so I created this blog post as a reference.</p>
<h2 class="anchor anchorWithStickyNavbar_LWe7" id="truncating-the-summary-of-a-blog-post">Truncating the summary of a blog post<a href="https://rajathjn.github.io/blogsite/blog/mdx-blog-post#truncating-the-summary-of-a-blog-post" class="hash-link" aria-label="Direct link to Truncating the summary of a blog post" title="Direct link to Truncating the summary of a blog post">​</a></h2>
<p>Use a <code>&lt;!--</code> <code>truncate</code> <code>--&gt;</code> comment to limit blog post size in the list view for md.</p>
<p>Use a <code>{/*</code> <code>truncate</code> <code>*/}</code> comment to limit blog post size in the list view for mdx.</p>
<!-- -->
<h2 class="anchor anchorWithStickyNavbar_LWe7" id="blog-post-features">Blog post features<a href="https://rajathjn.github.io/blogsite/blog/mdx-blog-post#blog-post-features" class="hash-link" aria-label="Direct link to Blog post features" title="Direct link to Blog post features">​</a></h2>
<p>Blog posts support <a href="https://docusaurus.io/docs/markdown-features" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">Docusaurus Markdown features</a>, such as <a href="https://mdxjs.com/" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">MDX</a>.</p>
